<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9805> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9805" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/25> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 257-63" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7591> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7591" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. pl. 44. His action when, as prefect or legate, he was in command of several cohorts in the battle of Alexandria on March 27 (January 14), 47, was decisive (Bell. Alex. 31..1-3)Add notices in MRR 2.292, 47 B.C., and Index, 542.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6103> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6103" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "No title preserved. See 44, Tribunes of the Plebs. He served under Octavian and was sent in command of the praetorian cohort and the Martian legion in order to protect Pansa's approach to Mutina. He probably-perished in the battle of Forum Gallorum (App. BC 3.66-69, #; cf. Cic. Fam. 10.33.4, and 30.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5972> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5972" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He was excluded, like Ti. Cannutius, from the meeting of the Senate on November 28, presumably because he also was a Tribune of the Plebs and Antony wished to prevent a veto (Cic. Phil. 3.23; cf. Att. 15.4.1)." .
